Package labyrinth

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Movable
    Interface that describes an object that can move or be moved.
    MovableObserver
    Interface that describes an object that is needed for each Mobable object.
    TerminalObserver.OnClickListener
    Interface that should be implemented in order to be able to receive notifications from TerminalObserver.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Direction
    Class that represents direction in two-dimensional system.
    Enter
    Class that represents enter of labyrinth.
    Exit
    Game object that represent exit of the labyrinth.
    Game
    Class, that contains logic of the game.
    GameObject
    Class that represents single drawable object of labyrinth.
    Keys
    Game object that represents keys.
    Labyrinth
    Class, that displays map of the labyrinth on the terminal window
    Monster
    Abstract class for representing all monsters that can live in labyrinth.
    Mover
    Class that can move Movable object in some Direction.
    MovingMonster
    Class that represents a monster that can move inside of labyrinth.
    Player
    Class that represents a player of the labyrinth.
    Position
    Class that represents position of the object in the labyrinth.
    Road
    Class that represents a road of labyrinth.
    StaticMonster
    Class that represents a monster that can not move.
    TerminalObserver
    Class that listens for user input.
    Wall
    Class that represents a wall of labyrinth.
